e web | url=https://ew.com/movies/onward-deleted-scene-sirens-jenny-tom-holland | title=Exclusive: 'Onward' deleted scene summons sirens and a lost character | access-date=April 2, 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328104405/https://ew.com/movies/onward-deleted-scene-sirens-jenny-tom-holland/ | archive-date=March 28, 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/onward-deleted-scene-features-a-capitalist-twist-on-the-1842526629 | title=Onward Deleted Scene Features a Capitalist Twist on the Siren Song | access-date=April 3, 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331032039/https://io9.gizmodo.com/onward-deleted-scene-features-a-capitalist-twist-on-the-1842526629 | archive-date=March 31, 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n===Theatrical===\n''Onward'' premiered at the [[70th Berlin International Film Festival]] on February 21, 2020<ref name=premiere>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/berlin-film-festival-lineup-competition-announced-revealed-live-1202845048/|website=[[Deadline.com]]|last=Wiseman|first=Andreas|date=January 29, 2020|title=Berlin Competition Lineup: Kelly Reichardt, Sally Potter, Abel Ferrara, Christian Petzold; Disney's 'Onward' & Hillary Clinton Also Heading To Fest|accessdate=February 16, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130153631/https://deadline.com/2020/01/berlin-film-festival-lineup-competition-announced-revealed-live-1202845048/|archive-date=January 30, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and was released in the United States on March 6.<ref name=\"VarietyDec2018\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/chris-pratt-tom-holland-julia-louis-dreyfus-octavia-spencer-onward-1203088174/ |title=Chris Pratt, Tom Holland, Julia Louis-Dreyfus, Octavia Spencer to Voice Pixar's 'Onward' |last1=McNary |first1=Dave |date=December 12, 2018 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |accessdate=December 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181212222451/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/chris-pratt-tom-holland-julia-louis-dreyfus-octavia-spencer-onward-1203088174/|archive-date=December 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> A new short film titled ''[[Playdate with Destiny]]'', centered around [[Maggie Simpson]] of ''[[The Simpsons]]'', appears before the feature film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/simpsons-short-film/|title=New 'The Simpsons' Short Film To Play In Theaters In Front of Pixar's 'Onward'|date=February 28, 2020|access-date=February 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228181730/https://www.slashfilm.com/simpsons-short-film/|archive-date=February 28, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B9GRqCFnI6M/|title=Maggie Simpson is speechless... Playdate with Destiny, a new Simpsons short film before Disney & Pixar's Onward. Exclusively in theaters! #TheSimpsons|author=thesimpsons on [[Instagram]]|date=February 27, 2020|access-date=February 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228061700/https://www.instagram.com/p/B9GRqCFnI6M/|archive-date=February 28, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n''Onward'' was released [[Digital distribution|digitally]] on the night of March 20, 2020 and became available for [[Disney+]] subscribers on April 3, 2020 in the United States. The announcement followed Disney's earlier than planned release of ''[[Frozen II]]'' on Disney+ due to the  [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://collider.com/onward-digital-release-disney-plus-details/ |title=Pixar's ''Onward'' Is Getting an Early Digital and Disney+ Release |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |last=Gemmill |first=Allie|date=March 20, 2020 |accessdate=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Over its first week of home release, the film was the sixth-most watched on [[Prime Video|Amazon Prime]] and second-most on the [[iTunes Store]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/farewell-box-office-premium-vod-charts-bloodshot-onward-birds-of-prey-1202220714/|title='Farewell, Box Office: This Was the Week That Premium VOD Charts Took Flight|website=[[IndieWire]]|first=Tom|last=Brueggemann|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=March 27, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327152429/https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/farewell-box-office-premium-vod-charts-bloodshot-onward-birds-of-prey-1202220714/|archive-date=March 27, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In Australia, it will be released on Disney+ on April 24, 2020 and will be available on DVD on May 19, 2020.<ref name=\"ausrelease\">{{cite web|url=https://tvtonight.com.au/2020/03/airdate-onward.html|title=Airdate: ''Onward''|work=TV Tonight|last=Knox|first=David|date=March 31, 2020|access-date=April 5, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401055617/https://tvtonight.com.au/2020/03/airdate-onward.html|archive-date=April 1, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=McClintock |first=Pamela |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-release-onward-early-digital-coronavirus-pandemic-1285590 |title=Disney to Release 'Onward' Early on Digital Amid Coronavirus Pandemic |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=March 20, 2020 |accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing==\nIn May 2019, two stills from the film, featuring Barley, Ian and their mother, were revealed. The following day, the film's teaser poster was released, and the teaser trailer debuted during [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s broadcast of the [[2019 NBA Finals]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/onward-disney-pixar-trailer-poster-1202624788/ |title=Disney/Pixar 'Onward' Bows First-Look Trailer During NBA Finals Game 1 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |last=Haring |first=Bruce |date=May 30, 2019 |accessdate=June 12, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531044356/https://deadline.com/2019/05/onward-disney-pixar-trailer-poster-1202624788/|archive-date=May 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The trailer was also shown with ''[[Toy Story 4]]'' and ''[[Spider-Man: Far From Home]]''. Official trailers were released in October and December 2019.\n\n== Lawsuit ==\nIn January 2020, San Francisco tattoo artist Sweet Cecily Daniher filed a copyright lawsuit against Disney, Pixar, and ''Onward'' producer Kori Rae. In September 2018, Pixar rented Daniher's \"Vanicorn\", a van decorated with a unicorn-themed mural, for use in a one-day festival. She learned about the production of ''Onward'' in May 2019 and, after seeing images of the van used by Ian and Barley Lightfoot in the film, came to believe that Pixar had copied the design of the Vanicorn in violation of her rental agreement with the company, as well as the [[Digital Millennium Copyright Act]], the [[Visual Artists Rights Act]], and the California Artists Protection Act. She sought in her suit to prohibit distribution of the film and any infringing advertisements or merchandise.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/disney-sued-by-artist-unicorn-adorned-van-pixars-onward-1274131|title=Artist Sues Disney, Pixar Over Unicorn-Adorned Van in 'Onward'|last=Cullins|first=Ashley|date=January 28, 2020|website=The Hollywood Reporter|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129154442/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/disney-sued-by-artist-unicorn-adorned-van-pixars-onward-1274131|archive-date=January 29, 2020|access-date=February 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n''Onward'' grossed $61.6 million in the United States and Canada, and $41.6 million in other territories, for a worldwide total of $103.2 million.<ref name=\"BOM\"/> It was speculated the gross for the film was significantly [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema|affected by the coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/mar/16/coronavirus-cinema-audiences-decline-film-industry |title=Cinema audiences drop dramatically as coronavirus restrictions bite |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317010316/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/mar/16/coronavirus-cinema-audiences-decline-film-industry |archive-date=March 17, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/onward-the-hunt-invisible-man-box-office-coronavirus-1203534409/ |title=Box Office: 'Onward' Leads as Coronavirus Stunts North American Sales |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314224942/https://variety.com/2020/film/news/onward-the-hunt-invisible-man-box-office-coronavirus-1203534409/ |archive-date=March 14, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a31659709/onward-box-office-bloodshot-coronavirus-cinemas/ |title=Bloodshot and Onward suffer during worst US box office weekend in 22 years |date=March 16, 2020 |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324144029/https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a31659709/onward-box-office-bloodshot-coronavirus-cinemas/ |archive-date=March 24, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn the United States and Canada, the film was released alongside ''[[The Way Back (2020 film)|The Way Back]]'' and the wide expansion of ''[[Emma (2020 film)|Emma]]'', and was projected to gross $45\u201350 million from 4,200 theaters in its opening weekend.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/onward-ben-affleck-the-way-back-box-office-coronavirus-1202873492/ |title=Disney-Pixar's 'Onward' Eyes $100M Global Start, Even With Coronavirus Concerns |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |first2=Nancy |last2=Tartaglione |date=March 3, 2020 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=March 4, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304013005/https://deadline.com/2020/03/onward-ben-affleck-the-way-back-box-office-coronavirus-1202873492/ |archive-date=March 4, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film held early advance screenings on February 29, and made $650,000 from 470 theaters.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2020/03/01/onward-pixar-my-hero-academia-impractical-jokers-wendy-weekend-box-office/#449321631858 |title= Weekend Box Office: 'Onward' Sells Out, 'My Hero Academia' Surprises And 'Wendy' Flops |first= Scott |last= Mendleson |date= March 1, 2020 |accessdate= March 4, 2020 |website= [[Forbes]] |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303203235/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2020/03/01/onward-pixar-my-hero-academia-impractical-jokers-wendy-weekend-box-office/#449321631858 |archive-date= March 3, 2020 |url-status= live }}</ref> It then made $12.1 million on its first day, including $2 million from Thursday night previews. The film went on to debut to $39.1 million, topping the box office but marking the third-ever lowest start for a Pixar film.<ref name=opening>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/onward-opening-weekend-disney-pixar-coronavirus-invisible-man-1202876016/ |title='Onward' Seeing Blas\u00e9 $40M Domestic Opening, $68M WW: Are Coronavirus Fears Impacting B.O.? \u2013 Sunday Update |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |date=March 7, 2020 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=March 7, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307021204/https://deadline.com/2020/03/onward-opening-weekend-disney-pixar-coronavirus-invisible-man-1202876016/ |archive-date=March 7, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=IndieWireOpen>{{cite web|title=Pixar's 'Onward' Opens to Modest Box Office With Weekend Down $100 Million From Last Year|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/pixar-onward-box-office-weekend-1202216191/|publisher=[[IndieWire]]|date=March 7, 2020|accessdate=March 7, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312131725/https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/pixar-onward-box-office-weekend-1202216191/|archive-date=March 12, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> While the film remained in first in its second weekend, it dropped 73% to $10.5 million (the worst-ever second weekend for a Pixar film), and was part of the lowest total-grossing weekend since October 1998, with all films combining for just $55.3 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/vin-diesel-bloodshot-i-still-believe-the-hunt-weekend-box-office-coronavirus-1202882333/|title=Weekend Box Office Headed To 22-Year-Low At $58M+ As Coronavirus Fears Grip Nation|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|accessdate=March 15, 2020|date=March 15, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315033857/https://deadline.com/2020/03/vin-diesel-bloodshot-i-still-believe-the-hunt-weekend-box-office-coronavirus-1202882333/|archive-date=March 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In the film's third weekend, due to the mass theater closures around the country, it made $71,000 from 135 locations, mostly [[drive-in theater|drive-ins]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/coronavirus-drive-in-movie-theaters-exhibition-shutdown-onward-1202890329/ |title=Drive-Ins Continue To Post Best Ticket Sales In Weekend Box Office Wiped Out By Theater Closures |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |date=March 23, 2020 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=March 24, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323212827/https://deadline.com/2020/03/coronavirus-drive-in-movie-theaters-exhibition-shutdown-onward-1202890329/ |archive-date=March 23, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\nOn [[review aggregator]] [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 88% based on 301 reviews, with an average rating of 7.15/10. The website's critics consensus reads: \"It may suffer in comparison to Pixar's classics, but ''Onward'' makes effective use of the studio's formula \u2013 and stands on its own merits as a funny, heartwarming, dazzlingly animated adventure.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/onward/|title=Onward (2020)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|access-date=April 17, 2020|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a weighted average score of 61 out of 100, based on 56 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/onward|title=Onward Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|access-date=April 17, 2020|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\u2013\" on an A+ to F scale (tied with ''[[Cars 2]]'' for the lowest score received by a Pixar film), and [[PostTrak]] reported filmgoers gave it 4.5 out of 5 stars.<ref name=opening/>\n\n[[Peter Bradshaw]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave it three out of five stars, and called the movie \"a likable family comedy that finds an easy rhythm without effort\" although felt that movie's \"attitude towards death\" is not radically powerful as in ''[[Coco (2017 film)|Coco]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/mar/06/onward-review-pixar-conjures-big-screen-adventure-with-wizard-quest-story|title=Onward review \u2013 Pixar conjures big-screen adventure with wizard quest story|last=Bradshaw|first=Peter|date=March 17, 2020|website=theguardian.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317081813/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/mar/06/onward-review-pixar-conjures-big-screen-adventure-with-wizard-quest-story|archive-date=March 17, 2020|access-date=}}</ref> In a same star review [[Peter Travers]] of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' said \"It\u2019s no ''Toy Story'' \u2014 but the animation juggernaut\u2019s latest, about two elf brothers on a quest, is still worth your while.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/onward-movie-review-pixar-960479/|title='Onward' Review: Pixar's Elf-Family Fantasy Is Light on Company's Magic|last=Travers|first=Peter|date=March 8, 2020|website=Rollingstone.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318070138/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/onward-movie-review-pixar-960479/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|access-date=}}</ref> [[James Berardinelli]], in his review  praised its originality, emotional weight and called it \"engaging and enjoyable\", and that \"There\u2019s something here for everyone\", though concluded that it isn't a next Disney/Pixar classic.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reelviews.net/reelviews/onward |title=Onward (United States, 2020) |last=Berardinelli |first=James |date=March 6, 2020 |website=Reelviews |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318072235/https://www.reelviews.net/reelviews/onward |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Ben Travis of ''[[Empire Magazine]]'' gave the film a five out of five stars and said: \"Pixar returns with a great big power-chord of a movie \u2014 heart-pumping, resonant, and positively harmonious.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Travis |first=Ben |url=https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/onward/ |title=Onward Review &#124; Movie |work=Empire |date=February 21, 2020 |accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Richard Roeper]] of the ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' called ''Onward'' a step back for Pixar, giving it two out of four stars. He said, \"The story fluctuates between the uninspired and the just plain weird and then gets even weirder.\" While he praised the animation and said that the movie \"begins with an intriguing premise\", he concluded that it \"doesn't come close to fully fleshing out the possibilities\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/2020/2/27/21152865/onward-review-worst-pixar-movie-disney-tom-holland-chris-pratt|title='Onward' a step backward for Disney-Pixar|last=Roeper|first=Richard|date=March 17, 2020|website=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311015050/https://chicago.suntimes.com/2020/2/27/21152865/onward-review-worst-pixar-movie-disney-tom-holland-chris-pratt|archive-date=March 11, 2020|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Ban and censorship ===\n<!-- There is a likelihood the film was banned in these countries for the depiction of necromancy, as the LGBT reference is very minor and can be cut. -->\nThe film was banned in the [[Arab world|Arab]] countries of [[Kuwait]], [[Oman]], [[Qatar]], and [[Saudi Arabia]], as one female cyclops police officer character in the film named Specter (voiced by Lena Waithe) briefly indicates that she is a [[lesbian]]. The scene in question is a brief scene in which Colt Bronco is lamenting about how Ian and Barley Lightfoot do not respect him as a father figure. Specter then replies to him by saying, \"It's not easy being a new parent\u2014my girlfriend's daughter got me pulling my hair out, okay?\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/disney-onward-banned-multiple-middle-east-markets-lesbian-lgbt-reference-1202876168/|title=Disney/Pixar's 'Onward' Banned In Multiple Middle East Countries Due To Lesbian Reference|last=Wiseman|first=Andreas|date=March 6, 2020|website=Deadline|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307021916/https://deadline.com/2020/03/disney-onward-banned-multiple-middle-east-markets-lesbian-lgbt-reference-1202876168/|archive-date=March 7, 2020|access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/onward-banned-lesbian-kuwait-oman-qatar-saudi-arabia-1203526359/|title='Onward' Banned in Several Middle East Countries Due to Lesbian Reference|last=McNary|first=Dave|date=March 6, 2020|website=Variety|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307131642/https://variety.com/2020/film/news/onward-banned-lesbian-kuwait-oman-qatar-saudi-arabia-1203526359/|archive-date=March 7, 2020|access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/onward-banned-middle-east-gay-reference-1202216026/|title='Onward' Banned in Multiple Middle Eastern Countries, Censored in Russia for Gay Reference|last=Lattanzio|first=Ryan|date=March 6, 2020|website=Indie Wire|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319030705/https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/onward-banned-middle-east-gay-reference-1202216026/|archive-date=March 19, 2020|access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref> Homosexual acts are criminalized in these four aforementioned countries, which are predominantly Muslim, although Kuwait does not criminalize female homosexual acts. However, this ban is not universal, and the film has been screened in [[Bahrain]], the [[United Arab Emirates]], [[Lebanon]], and [[Egypt]].\n\nIn [[Russia]], where the [[Russian gay propaganda law|gay propaganda law]] officially criminalizes the dissemination of LGBT-related content to minors under 18, the Russian dub, handled by [[Disney Character Voices International]], changed the line to \"It's not easy being a new parent\u2014my partner's daughter got me pulling my hair out, okay?\" instead. The Russian dub also avoided referring to Specter with gender-specific pronouns.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official|https://movies.disney.com/onward}}\n* {{IMDb title|7146812}}\n\n{{Disney theatrical animated features}}\n{{Pixar}}\n{{Dan Scanlon}}\n\n[[Category:2020 3D films]]\n[[Category:2020 computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:2020 fantasy films]]\n[[Category:2020s American animated films]]\n[[Category:2020s animated films]]\n[[Category:2020s computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:2020s fantasy-comedy films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:American animated fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy-comedy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:Cartoon controversies]]\n[[Category:Censored films]]\n[[Category:Epic fantasy films]]\n[[Category:Films about brothers]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Dan Scanlon]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Jeff Danna]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Mychael Danna]]\n[[Category:Films set on fictional planets]]\n[[Category:High fantasy films]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related animated films]]\n[[Category:Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema]]\n[[Category:Pixar animated films]]\n[[Category:Walt Disney Pictures films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 film directed by Dan Scanlon}}\n{{Use American English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Onward\n| image          = Onward poster.jpg\n| border         = no\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Dan Scanlon]]\n| producer       = [[Kori Rae]]\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* Dan Scanlon\n* Jason Headley\n* [[Keith Bunin]]\n}}\n| story          = {{Plainlist|\n* Dan Scanlon\n* Keith Bunin\n* Jason Headley\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Tom Holland (actor)|Tom Holland]]\n* [[Chris Pratt]]\n* [[Julia Louis-Dreyfus]]\n* [[Octavia Spencer]]\n}}\n| music          = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Mychael Danna]]<ref name=\"DannaScore\">{{cite web |url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2019/04/16/mychael-jeff-danna-to-score-pixars-onward/ |title=Mychael & Jeff Danna to Score Pixar's 'Onward' \u2013 Film Music Reporter |publisher=|access-date=April 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417121323/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2019/04/16/mychael-jeff-danna-to-score-pixars-onward/|archive-date=April 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Jeff Danna]]<ref name=\"DannaScore\" />\n}}\n| cinematography = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Sharon Calahan]]\n* Adam Habib\n}}\n| editing        = Catherine Apple<ref>{{cite web|title=Catherine Apple|date=December 7, 2019|url=https://collider.com/how-does-pixar-make-movies-ccxp/|publisher=collider|accessdate=December 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207221911/https://collider.com/how-does-pixar-make-movies-ccxp/|archive-date=December 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Walt Disney Pictures]]\n* [[Pixar Animation Studios]]\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Walt Disney Studios<br />Motion Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|2|21|[[Berlin International Film Festival|Berlinale]]|2020|3|6|United States}}\n| runtime        = 103 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.berlinale.de/en/programme/programme/detail.html?film_id=202012642|title=Programme - Onward|website=[[Berlin International Film Festival|Berlinale]]|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200216234513/https://www.berlinale.de/en/programme/programme/detail.html?film_id=202012642|archive-date=February 16, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $175\u2013200 million<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/box-office-onward-international-coronavirus-1203527183/|title=Box Office: 'Onward' Debuts to $28 Million Overseas Amid Coronavirus Outbreak|first=Rebecca|last=Rubin|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 8, 2020|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308192742/https://variety.com/2020/film/news/box-office-onward-international-coronavirus-1203527183/|archive-date=March 8, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| gross          = $103.2 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl3433267713/?ref_=bo_hm_rs |title=Onward (2020) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |access-date=April 10, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229183631/https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl3433267713/?ref_=bo_hm_rs |archive-date=February 29, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Onward''''' is a 2020 American [[computer-animated]] [[urban fantasy]] film produced by [[Pixar Animation Studios]] for [[Walt Disney Pictures]]. The film is directed by [[Dan Scanlon]], produced by [[Kori Rae]] from a screenplay written by Scanlon, Jason Headley, and [[Keith Bunin]], and stars the voices of [[Tom Holland (actor)|Tom Holland]], [[Chris Pratt]], [[Julia Louis-Dreyfus]], and [[Octavia Spencer]]. Set in a suburban fantasy world, the film follows two elf brothers who set out on a quest to find an artifact that will bring back their deceased father.<ref name=\"Synopsis\">{{cite news |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/pixar-disney-untitled-suburban-fantasy-world-unicorns-d23-1202496455/ |title=D23: Pixar Announces Untitled Quest Movie Set in 'Suburban Fantasy World' |last=Variety staff |date=July 14, 2017 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=July 21, 2017 |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170715013545/https://variety.com/2017/film/news/pixar-disney-untitled-suburban-fantasy-world-unicorns-d23-1202496455/|archive-date=July 15, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe film premiered at the [[70th Berlin International Film Festival]] on February 21, 2020 and was released in the United States on March 6. It received generally positive reviews from critics and has grossed $103 million worldwide. The film's financial shortcomings were attributed to the [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema|2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], which resulted in theaters around the globe being closed. Like several other films released in March, it was made available digitally two weeks after its theatrical release.\n\n==Plot==\nIn a world inhabited by [[Legendary creature|mythical creatures]], magic was once commonplace, though difficult to master. After technological advances over the years, magic became obsolete and was largely discarded.\n\nIn a time equivalent to the modern day, Ian Lightfoot, an [[elf]] high-schooler lacking self-confidence, and his older brother Barley, a history and [[role-playing game]] fanatic, live in the city of New Mushroomton. Their father Wilden died shortly before Ian was born, and their mother Laurel has a new boyfriend, [[centaur]] police officer Colt Bronco, whom both Ian and Barley dislike.\n\nOn Ian's sixteenth birthday, Laurel gives the brothers a gift from Wilden: a magical staff, a rare gem, and a letter describing a \"visitation spell\" that can resurrect their father for a single day. Ian accidentally succeeds in casting the spell, but only the lower half of Wilden's body is reformed before the gem disintegrates. The brothers embark on a quest to acquire another gem and complete the spell, taking Barley's beloved [[van]] \"Guinevere\". Finding the boys gone, Laurel leaves to find them.\n\nIan and Barley visit the [[Manticore]]\u2019s Tavern, named for a monster possessing a map to the gem. The tavern has become a [[family restaurant]] managed by the Manticore, legally named The Manticore, also known as \"Corey\". Arguing with Ian over the map, The Manticore realizes how boring her life has become and drives the customers away in a fit of rage, accidentally setting fire to the restaurant and the map. The brothers' only clue to the gem is a children's menu suggesting \"Raven's Point\", a nearby mountain. Laurel later arrives at the scene and befriends The Manticore, who agrees to help her. The Manticore warns that the brothers' journey may awaken a curse that can only be defeated by her special sword, which she and Laurel steal from a [[Pawnbroker|pawn shop]].\n\nTraveling to the mountains, Ian and Barley narrowly escape the police and a [[Outlaw motorcycle club|motorcycle gang]] of [[pixie]]s,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sims |first1=David |title=Pixar Needs to Make More Movies Like 'Onward' |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/culture/archive/2020/02/onward-movie-review-dan-scanlon-chris-pratt/606736/ |website=The Atlantic |accessdate=22 March 2020 |date=21 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225005110/https://www.theatlantic.com/culture/archive/2020/02/onward-movie-review-dan-scanlon-chris-pratt/606736/ |archive-date=February 25, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> relying on Ian's newly awakened spell-casting abilities and Barley's role-playing game instincts. \"Raven's Point\" leads them on a trail indicated by a series of [[raven]] statues, but Colt follows them, calling in reinforcements. Barley sacrifices Guinevere to cause a landslide, blocking their pursuers. Following the statues, the brothers descend through a cave and avoid a series of traps and deadly creatures, surfacing to find themselves in front of Ian's high school. Ian lashes out at Barley for leading them on a wild goose chase and walks away with Wilden.\n\nRereading his list of things he always wished to do with his father, Ian realizes that Barley has been a father figure throughout his entire life, and returns to make amends. Barley discovers the gem inside a historic fountain and retrieves it, unwittingly triggering the curse The Manticore spoke of, which turns the high school into an artificial dragon bent on claiming the gem. Ian faces the artificial dragon, but his staff is knocked into the ocean; he reforms it from a splinter and continues the fight. The Manticore flies in carrying Laurel, who plunges the magic sword into the artificial dragon's heart, buying Ian time to cast the visitation spell and fully reform Wilden's body. Ian sends Barley ahead to give his goodbye to Wilden, and holds off the artificial dragon long enough for Laurel to destroy it. After Wilden dissipates, Barley tells Ian that their father is proud of him, and the brothers share a hug.\n\nIan's confidence and spell-casting improve and he surprises Barley by painting his new van, the \"Guinevere 2\". The Manticore reopens her tavern in its original spirit, drawing in customers with tales of past adventures, and Ian and Barley continue questing.\n\n==Voice cast==\n{{cast listing|\n* [[Tom Holland (actor)|Tom Holland]] as Ian Lightfoot,<ref name=VarietyDec2018/><ref name=firstlook /> a teenaged [[elf]] who is Barley's younger brother and Laurel and Wilden's son.\n* [[Chris Pratt]] as Barley Lightfoot,<ref name=VarietyDec2018/><ref name=firstlook>{{cite web |url=https://www.pixarpost.com/2019/05/pixar-onward-first-look.html |title=Breaking: First Look at Characters Ian and Barley Lightfoot from Pixar's Suburban Fantasy Film, 'Onward' (In Theaters March 6, 2020) |author=Pixar Post |publisher=|access-date=May 29, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190529172427/https://www.pixarpost.com/2019/05/pixar-onward-first-look.html|archive-date=May 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Ian's older brother, and Laurel and Wilden's son who longs for a magical quest.\n* [[Julia Louis-Dreyfus]] as Laurel Lightfoot,<ref name=VarietyDec2018/><ref name=firstlook /><ref name=\"Clips\">{{cite web |url=https://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/pixar-onward-chris-pratt-tom-holland/ |title=D23: Pixar Brings New Onward Clips |last=White |first=James |date=August 25, 2019 |website=[[Empire (film magazine)|Empire]] |accessdate=August 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825105550/https://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/pixar-onward-chris-pratt-tom-holland/|archive-date=August 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> the widowed mother of Ian and Barley.\n* [[Octavia Spencer]] as The \"Corey\" Manticore, a [[manticore]] restaurant owner and former adventurer whom Ian and Barley go to for help on their quest.\n* [[Mel Rodriguez]] as Colt Bronco, a [[centaur]] police officer and Laurel's new husband.<ref name=twit3600/>\n* [[Kyle Bornheimer]] as Wilden Lightfoot, Ian and Barley's late father and Laurel's late husband.<ref name=\"WholeCast\" />\n* [[Lena Waithe]] as Specter, a [[cyclops]] police officer.<ref name=twit3600/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://insidethemagic.net/2020/02/onward-first-openly-lgbtq-bt1/|title=Disney-Pixar's \"Onward\" Will Feature the First Openly LGBTQ Character|date=February 22, 2020|via=Inside the Magic|access-date=February 22, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222040111/https://insidethemagic.net/2020/02/onward-first-openly-lgbtq-bt1/|archive-date=February 22, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2020/02/24/pixars-first-out-gay-character-to-be-voiced-by-lena-waithe-in-onward/|title=Pixar's first out gay character to be voiced by Lena Waithe in 'Onward'|last=Frishberg|first=Hannah|date=February 24, 2020|website=[[New York Post]]|access-date=February 25, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225133013/https://nypost.com/2020/02/24/pixars-first-out-gay-character-to-be-voiced-by-lena-waithe-in-onward/|archive-date=February 25, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Ali Wong]] as Gore, a [[faun]] police officer.<ref name=twit3600>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/pixaronward/status/1206620188709273600|title=Behold: Character posters for #PixarOnward, including newly-announced cast @AliWong, @LenaWaithe, and @_MelRodriguez_.\u2728 Check back tomorrow to see the brand-new trailer for the film|via=[[Twitter]]|access-date=December 16, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191217032256/https://twitter.com/pixaronward/status/1206620188709273600|archive-date=December 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Grey DeLisle|Grey Griffin]] as Dewdrop, a [[pixie]] and the leader of the Pixie Dusters [[Outlaw motorcycle club|biker gang]].<ref name=\"btva\"/>\n* [[Tracey Ullman]] as Grecklin, a [[goblin]] pawn shop owner.<ref name=\"WholeCast\" />\n* [[Wilmer Valderrama]] as Gaxton, an elf and college friend of Wilden.<ref name=\"WholeCast\" />\n* George Psarras as Avel, an elf police officer.<ref name=\"WholeCast\" />\n* [[John Ratzenberger]] as Fenwick, a cyclops construction worker.<ref name=\"WholeCast\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/snyde/ny-stars-attend-the-world-premiere-of-disney-pixar-onward-20200219-547inowgbnbhxnnziyywj3eu6a-photogallery.html|title=Stars attended the world premiere of Disney Pixar's \"Onward\" at the El Capitan Theatre on Feb. 18, 2020 in Hollywood, Calif.|website=New York Daily News|accessdate=February 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221191311/https://www.nydailynews.com/snyde/ny-stars-attend-the-world-premiere-of-disney-pixar-onward-20200219-547inowgbnbhxnnziyywj3eu6a-photogallery.html|archive-date=February 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Production ==\n===Development===\nIn July 2017, Pixar announced a \"suburban fantasy world\" film at the [[D23 Expo]], with Scanlon directing and Rae producing.<ref name=\"Synopsis\"/> The film was inspired by the death of Scanlon's father, when he and his brother were younger, and their relationship. He decided to write the story after hearing an audio clip of his father.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3025627/pixar-suburban-fantasy-film-dan-scanlon/ |title=Pixar's New 'Suburban Fantasy' Sounds Like A Real Tearjerker |last=Bell |first=Crystal |date=July 17, 2017 |website=[[MTV News]] |publisher=MTV|access-date=April 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170718003125/http://www.mtv.com/news/3025627/pixar-suburban-fantasy-film-dan-scanlon/|archive-date=July 18, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On December 12, 2018, the title was revealed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/pixar-moves-forward-with-suburban-fantasy-film-onward-cast-includes-chris-pratt-tom-holland |title=Pixar Moves Forward with Suburban Fantasy Film 'Onward'; Cast Includes Chris Pratt, Tom Holland |last=Weiss |first=Josh |date=December 12, 2018 |website=[[Syfy]] |publisher=[[NBCUniversal Cable Entertainment Group]] |accessdate=December 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181212222813/https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/pixar-moves-forward-with-suburban-fantasy-film-onward-cast-includes-chris-pratt-tom-holland|archive-date=December 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2019, Headley and Bunin were hired to rewrite the screenplay.\n\n===Casting===\nOn December 12, 2018, Holland, Pratt, Louis-Dreyfus and Spencer were announced as starring in the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/onward-pixar-movie-chris-pratt-tom-holland-julia-louis-dreyfus-octavia-spencer-cast-1202518598/ |title=Pixar's 'Onward' To Star Chris Pratt, Tom Holland, Julia Louis-Dreyfus & Octavia Spencer |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |date=December 12, 2018 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |accessdate=December 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181212221000/https://deadline.com/2018/12/onward-pixar-movie-chris-pratt-tom-holland-julia-louis-dreyfus-octavia-spencer-cast-1202518598/|archive-date=December 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> While having recorded most of their lines separately, Holland and Pratt did some of their recording sessions together since, according to Scanlon, \"they've worked together before and hung out together\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Falcone |first1=Dana Rose |title=See Chris Pratt, Julia Louis-Dreyfus & Tom Holland as Elves in Disney-Pixar's Onward: First Look! |url=https://www.people.com/movies/chris-pratt-julia-louis-dreyfus-tom-holland-onward/ |website=People |date=May 29, 2019|access-date=May 30, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190529215133/https://people.com/movies/chris-pratt-julia-louis-dreyfus-tom-holland-onward/|archive-date=May 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> According to Rae, Holland and Pratt improvised some of their lines while recording together.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a30415714/tom-holland-chris-pratt-onward-cast-interview/ |title=Marvel's Tom Holland and Chris Pratt being cast in Onward was \"dumb luck\" |date=January 6, 2020 |access-date=February 22, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222042437/https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a30415714/tom-holland-chris-pratt-onward-cast-interview/ |archive-date=February 22, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On December 17, 2019, Wong, Waithe and Rodriguez joined the cast of the film.<ref name=twit3600/> On February 18, 2020, Valderrama, Ullman, Bornheimer, Psarras and Ratzenberger were revealed to have been cast in the film.<ref name=\"WholeCast\"/>\n\n===Music===\nOn April 16, 2019, [[Mychael Danna|Mychael]] and [[Jeff Danna]] were revealed to be the film's composers.<ref name=\"DannaScore\"/> On February 12, 2020, [[Brandi Carlile]] revealed she recorded the song \"Carried Me With You\" for the film's end credits. She co-wrote it with Phil and Tim Hanseroth.<ref name=\"variety1\">{{cite news |last1=Willman |first1=Chris |title=Brandi Carlile Records Theme Song for Pixar Pic 'Onward' |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/brandi-carlile-records-theme-song-pixar-onward-1203502224/ |accessdate=17 February 2020 |magazine=Variety |date=12 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200214151349/https://variety.com/2020/film/news/brandi-carlile-records-theme-song-pixar-onward-1203502224/ |archive-date=February 14, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film's soundtrack was released on February 28, 2020.<ref name=\"variety1\"/>\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = '''''Onward: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack'''''\n| extra_column = Performer\n| all_music = [[Mychael Danna]] and [[Jeff Danna]], except where noted\n| total_length = 1:02:32\n\n| title1 = Carried Me with You\n| writer1 = [[Brandi Carlile]], Phil and Tim Hanseroth\n| extra1 = Carlile\n| length1 = 3:33\n\n| title2 = Quests of Yore\n| length2 = 0:52\n\n| title3 = The World Was Full of Wonder\n| length3 = 1:37\n\n| title4 = A Little Magic\n| length4 = 0:43\n\n| title5 = Bad Dragon\n| length5 = 1:03\n\n| title6 = New Ian\n| length6 = 2:36\n\n| title7 = My Mighty Steed\n| length7 = 0:22\n\n| title8 = My Birthday Is Cancelled\n| length8 = 0:44\n\n| title9 = Wish I Could Spend the Day with You\n| length9 = 1:46\n\n| title10 = The Visitation Spell\n| length10 = 3:35\n\n| title11 = The Spell\n| length11 = 1:06\n\n| title12 = The Spell Only Lasts One Day\n| length12 = 0:56\n\n| title13 = Find Another Phoenix Gem\n| length13 = 0:49\n\n| title14 = Going on a Quest\n| length14 = 0:24\n\n| title15 = Laurel in Pursuit\n| length15 = 0:44\n\n| title16 = The Manticore's Tavern\n| length16 = 0:43\n\n| title17 = Tavern Remodeling\n| length17 = 1:12\n\n| title18 = The Map to Raven's Point\n| length18 = 1:45\n\n| title19 = Two Teenage Elves\n| length19 = 0:38\n\n| title20 = Magnora Gantuan!\n| length20 = 0:32\n\n| title21 = Baby Legs\n| length21 = 0:41\n\n| title22 = Pixie Dusters\n| length22 = 1:18\n\n| title23 = The Guardian Curse\n| length23 = 0:42\n\n| title24 = Driving Test\n| length24 = 3:17\n\n| title25 = Dance Fight\n| length25 = 2:22\n\n| title26 = Path of Peril\n| length26 = 0:41\n\n| title27 = Pawn Shop\n| length27 = 0:28\n\n| title28 = Tracking Guinevere\n| length28 = 1:04\n\n| title29 = Bottomless Pit\n| length29 = 0:56\n\n| title30 = The Trust Bridge\n| length30 = 1:20\n\n| title31 = Follow Your Gut\n| length31 = 0:52\n\n| title32 = Running from the Cops\n| length32 = 1:59\n\n| title33 = Sacrifice\n| length33 = 0:59\n\n| title34 = Just a Beat Up Old Van\n| length34 = 1:36\n\n| title35 = The Cave\n| length35 = 0:54\n\n| title36 = Accelior!\n| length36 = 0:26\n\n| title37 = Boom Bastia!\n| length37 = 0:47\n\n| title38 = Barley's Last Memory of Dad\n| length38 = 0:58\n\n| title39 = Led Us to Our Victory!\n| length39 = 1:49\n\n| title40 = The Truth Comes Out\n| length40 = 0:39\n\n| title41 = Share My Life with Him\n| length41 = 3:24\n\n| title42 = Battling the Dragon\n| length42 = 3:03\n\n| title43 = Voltar Thunderseer!\n| length43 = 0:59\n\n| title44 = Dad\n| length44 = 2:52\n\n| title45 = Magic Returns\n| length45 = 2:48\n}}\n\n===Deleted scene===\nThere was a storyboard scene where Ian, Barley, and Wilden are joined with a goat girl in the journey. Ian and the goat girl come across a booth hosted by three evil mermaids. The mermaids sing their mesmerizing song to lure the two into staying in one of three houses put for rent. Ian tries to silence them with the staff but the spell is too weak. When Ian and the goat girl are finally in a trance, the mermaids place them in one of the houses. The house they are in starts to sink into the ground.\n\nThe goat girl was omitted because the filmmakers want the film to focus on the relationship between Ian and Barley. The scene itself was removed because the filmmakers felt it was too grim.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://ew.com/movies/onward-deleted-scene-sirens-jenny-tom-holland | title=Exclusive: 'Onward' deleted scene summons sirens and a lost character | access-date=April 2, 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328104405/https://ew.com/movies/onward-deleted-scene-sirens-jenny-tom-holland/ | archive-date=March 28, 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/onward-deleted-scene-features-a-capitalist-twist-on-the-1842526629 | title=Onward Deleted Scene Features a Capitalist Twist on the Siren Song | access-date=April 3, 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331032039/https://io9.gizmodo.com/onward-deleted-scene-features-a-capitalist-twist-on-the-1842526629 | archive-date=March 31, 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n===Theatrical===\n''Onward'' premiered at the [[70th Berlin International Film Festival]] on February 21, 2020<ref name=premiere>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/berlin-film-festival-lineup-competition-announced-revealed-live-1202845048/|website=[[Deadline.com]]|last=Wiseman|first=Andreas|date=January 29, 2020|title=Berlin Competition Lineup: Kelly Reichardt, Sally Potter, Abel Ferrara, Christian Petzold; Disney's 'Onward' & Hillary Clinton Also Heading To Fest|accessdate=February 16, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130153631/https://deadline.com/2020/01/berlin-film-festival-lineup-competition-announced-revealed-live-1202845048/|archive-date=January 30, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and was released in the United States on March 6.<ref name=\"VarietyDec2018\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/chris-pratt-tom-holland-julia-louis-dreyfus-octavia-spencer-onward-1203088174/ |title=Chris Pratt, Tom Holland, Julia Louis-Dreyfus, Octavia Spencer to Voice Pixar's 'Onward' |last1=McNary |first1=Dave |date=December 12, 2018 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |accessdate=December 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181212222451/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/chris-pratt-tom-holland-julia-louis-dreyfus-octavia-spencer-onward-1203088174/|archive-date=December 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> A new short film titled ''[[Playdate with Destiny]]'', centered around [[Maggie Simpson]] of ''[[The Simpsons]]'', appears before the feature film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/simpsons-short-film/|title=New 'The Simpsons' Short Film To Play In Theaters In Front of Pixar's 'Onward'|date=February 28, 2020|access-date=February 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228181730/https://www.slashfilm.com/simpsons-short-film/|archive-date=February 28, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B9GRqCFnI6M/|title=Maggie Simpson is speechless... Playdate with Destiny, a new Simpsons short film before Disney & Pixar's Onward. Exclusively in theaters! #TheSimpsons|author=thesimpsons on [[Instagram]]|date=February 27, 2020|access-date=February 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228061700/https://www.instagram.com/p/B9GRqCFnI6M/|archive-date=February 28, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n''Onward'' was released [[Digital distribution|digitally]] on the night of March 20, 2020 and became available for [[Disney+]] subscribers on April 3, 2020 in the United States. The announcement followed Disney's earlier than planned release of ''[[Frozen II]]'' on Disney+ due to the  [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://collider.com/onward-digital-release-disney-plus-details/ |title=Pixar's ''Onward'' Is Getting an Early Digital and Disney+ Release |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |last=Gemmill |first=Allie|date=March 20, 2020 |accessdate=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Over its first week of home release, the film was the sixth-most watched on [[Prime Video|Amazon Prime]] and second-most on the [[iTunes Store]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/farewell-box-office-premium-vod-charts-bloodshot-onward-birds-of-prey-1202220714/|title='Farewell, Box Office: This Was the Week That Premium VOD Charts Took Flight|website=[[IndieWire]]|first=Tom|last=Brueggemann|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=March 27, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327152429/https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/farewell-box-office-premium-vod-charts-bloodshot-onward-birds-of-prey-1202220714/|archive-date=March 27, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In Australia, it will be released on Disney+ on April 24, 2020 and will be available on DVD on May 19, 2020.<ref name=\"ausrelease\">{{cite web|url=https://tvtonight.com.au/2020/03/airdate-onward.html|title=Airdate: ''Onward''|work=TV Tonight|last=Knox|first=David|date=31 March 2020|access-date=5 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401055617/https://tvtonight.com.au/2020/03/airdate-onward.html|archive-date=April 1, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=McClintock |first=Pamela |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-release-onward-early-digital-coronavirus-pandemic-1285590 |title=Disney to Release 'Onward' Early on Digital Amid Coronavirus Pandemic |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=2020-03-20 |accessdate=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing==\nIn May 2019, two stills from the film, featuring Barley, Ian and their mother, were revealed. The following day, the film's teaser poster was released, and the teaser trailer debuted during [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s broadcast of the [[2019 NBA Finals]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/onward-disney-pixar-trailer-poster-1202624788/ |title=Disney/Pixar 'Onward' Bows First-Look Trailer During NBA Finals Game 1 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |last=Haring |first=Bruce |date=May 30, 2019 |accessdate=June 12, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531044356/https://deadline.com/2019/05/onward-disney-pixar-trailer-poster-1202624788/|archive-date=May 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The trailer was also shown with ''[[Toy Story 4]]'' and ''[[Spider-Man: Far From Home]]''. Official trailers were released in October and December 2019.\n\n== Lawsuit ==\nIn January 2020, San Francisco tattoo artist Sweet Cecily Daniher filed a copyright lawsuit against Disney, Pixar, and ''Onward'' producer Kori Rae. In September 2018, Pixar rented Daniher's \"Vanicorn\", a van decorated with a unicorn-themed mural, for use in a one-day festival. She learned about the production of ''Onward'' in May 2019 and, after seeing images of the van used by Ian and Barley Lightfoot in the film, came to believe that Pixar had copied the design of the Vanicorn in violation of her rental agreement with the company, as well as the [[Digital Millennium Copyright Act]], the [[Visual Artists Rights Act]], and the California Artists Protection Act. She sought in her suit to prohibit distribution of the film and any infringing advertisements or merchandise.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/disney-sued-by-artist-unicorn-adorned-van-pixars-onward-1274131|title=Artist Sues Disney, Pixar Over Unicorn-Adorned Van in 'Onward'|last=Cullins|first=Ashley|date=January 28, 2020|website=The Hollywood Reporter|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129154442/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/disney-sued-by-artist-unicorn-adorned-van-pixars-onward-1274131|archive-date=January 29, 2020|access-date=February 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n''Onward'' grossed $61.6 million in the United States and Canada, and $41.6 million in other territories, for a worldwide total of $103.2 million.<ref name=\"BOM\"/> It was speculated the gross for the film was significantly [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema|affected by the coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/mar/16/coronavirus-cinema-audiences-decline-film-industry |title=Cinema audiences drop dramatically as coronavirus restrictions bite |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317010316/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/mar/16/coronavirus-cinema-audiences-decline-film-industry |archive-date=March 17, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/onward-the-hunt-invisible-man-box-office-coronavirus-1203534409/ |title=Box Office: 'Onward' Leads as Coronavirus Stunts North American Sales |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314224942/https://variety.com/2020/film/news/onward-the-hunt-invisible-man-box-office-coronavirus-1203534409/ |archive-date=March 14, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a31659709/onward-box-office-bloodshot-coronavirus-cinemas/ |title=Bloodshot and Onward suffer during worst US box office weekend in 22 years |date=March 16, 2020 |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324144029/https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a31659709/onward-box-office-bloodshot-coronavirus-cinemas/ |archive-date=March 24, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn the United States and Canada, the film was released alongside ''[[The Way Back (2020 film)|The Way Back]]'' and the wide expansion of ''[[Emma (2020 film)|Emma]]'', and was projected to gross $45\u201350 million from 4,200 theaters in its opening weekend.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/onward-ben-affleck-the-way-back-box-office-coronavirus-1202873492/ |title=Disney-Pixar's 'Onward' Eyes $100M Global Start, Even With Coronavirus Concerns |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |first2=Nancy |last2=Tartaglione |date=March 3, 2020 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=March 4, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304013005/https://deadline.com/2020/03/onward-ben-affleck-the-way-back-box-office-coronavirus-1202873492/ |archive-date=March 4, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film held early advance screenings on February 29, and made $650,000 from 470 theaters.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2020/03/01/onward-pixar-my-hero-academia-impractical-jokers-wendy-weekend-box-office/#449321631858 |title= Weekend Box Office: 'Onward' Sells Out, 'My Hero Academia' Surprises And 'Wendy' Flops |first= Scott |last= Mendleson |date= March 1, 2020 |accessdate= March 4, 2020 |website= [[Forbes]] |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303203235/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2020/03/01/onward-pixar-my-hero-academia-impractical-jokers-wendy-weekend-box-office/#449321631858 |archive-date= March 3, 2020 |url-status= live }}</ref> It then made $12.1 million on its first day, including $2 million from Thursday night previews. The film went on to debut to $39.1 million, topping the box office but marking the third-ever lowest start for a Pixar film.<ref name=opening>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/onward-opening-weekend-disney-pixar-coronavirus-invisible-man-1202876016/ |title='Onward' Seeing Blas\u00e9 $40M Domestic Opening, $68M WW: Are Coronavirus Fears Impacting B.O.? \u2013 Sunday Update |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |date=March 7, 2020 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=March 7, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307021204/https://deadline.com/2020/03/onward-opening-weekend-disney-pixar-coronavirus-invisible-man-1202876016/ |archive-date=March 7, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=IndieWireOpen>{{cite web|title=Pixar's 'Onward' Opens to Modest Box Office With Weekend Down $100 Million From Last Year|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/pixar-onward-box-office-weekend-1202216191/|publisher=[[IndieWire]]|date=March 7, 2020|accessdate=March 7, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312131725/https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/pixar-onward-box-office-weekend-1202216191/|archive-date=March 12, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> While the film remained in first in its second weekend, it dropped 73% to $10.5 million (the worst-ever second weekend for a Pixar film), and was part of the lowest total-grossing weekend since October 1998, with all films combining for just $55.3 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/vin-diesel-bloodshot-i-still-believe-the-hunt-weekend-box-office-coronavirus-1202882333/|title=Weekend Box Office Headed To 22-Year-Low At $58M+ As Coronavirus Fears Grip Nation|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|accessdate=March 15, 2020|date=March 15, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315033857/https://deadline.com/2020/03/vin-diesel-bloodshot-i-still-believe-the-hunt-weekend-box-office-coronavirus-1202882333/|archive-date=March 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In the film's third weekend, due to the mass theater closures around the country, it made $71,000 from 135 locations, mostly [[drive-in theater|drive-ins]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/coronavirus-drive-in-movie-theaters-exhibition-shutdown-onward-1202890329/ |title=Drive-Ins Continue To Post Best Ticket Sales In Weekend Box Office Wiped Out By Theater Closures |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |date=March 23, 2020 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=March 24, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323212827/https://deadline.com/2020/03/coronavirus-drive-in-movie-theaters-exhibition-shutdown-onward-1202890329/ |archive-date=March 23, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\nOn [[review aggregator]] [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 88% based on 301 reviews, with an average rating of 7.15/10. The website's critics consensus reads: \"It may suffer in comparison to Pixar's classics, but ''Onward'' makes effective use of the studio's formula \u2013 and stands on its own merits as a funny, heartwarming, dazzlingly animated adventure.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/onward/|title=Onward (2020)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|access-date=April 17, 2020|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a weighted average score of 61 out of 100, based on 56 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/onward|title=Onward Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|access-date=April 17, 2020|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\u2013\" on an A+ to F scale (tied with ''[[Cars 2]]'' for the lowest score received by a Pixar film), and [[PostTrak]] reported filmgoers gave it 4.5 out of 5 stars.<ref name=opening/>\n\n[[Peter Bradshaw]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave it three out of five stars, and called the movie \"a likable family comedy that finds an easy rhythm without effort\" although felt that movie's \"attitude towards death\" is not radically powerful as in ''[[Coco (2017 film)|Coco]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/mar/06/onward-review-pixar-conjures-big-screen-adventure-with-wizard-quest-story|title=Onward review \u2013 Pixar conjures big-screen adventure with wizard quest story|last=Bradshaw|first=Peter|date=17 March 2020|website=theguardian.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317081813/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/mar/06/onward-review-pixar-conjures-big-screen-adventure-with-wizard-quest-story|archive-date=March 17, 2020|access-date=}}</ref> In a same star review [[Peter Travers]] of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' said \"It\u2019s no ''Toy Story'' \u2014 but the animation juggernaut\u2019s latest, about two elf brothers on a quest, is still worth your while.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/onward-movie-review-pixar-960479/|title='Onward' Review: Pixar's Elf-Family Fantasy Is Light on Company's Magic|last=Travers|first=Peter|date=8 March 2020|website=Rollingstone.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318070138/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/onward-movie-review-pixar-960479/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|access-date=}}</ref> [[James Berardinelli]], in his review  praised its originality, emotional weight and called it \"engaging and enjoyable\", and that \"There\u2019s something here for everyone\", though concluded that it isn't a next Disney/Pixar classic.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reelviews.net/reelviews/onward |title=Onward (United States, 2020) |last=Berardinelli |first=James |date=6 March 2020 |website=Reelviews |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318072235/https://www.reelviews.net/reelviews/onward |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Ben Travis of ''[[Empire Magazine]]'' gave the film a five out of five stars and said: \"Pixar returns with a great big power-chord of a movie \u2014 heart-pumping, resonant, and positively harmonious.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Travis |first=Ben |url=https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/onward/ |title=Onward Review &#124; Movie |work=Empire |date=2020-02-21 |accessdate=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n[[Richard Roeper]] of the ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' called ''Onward'' a step back for Pixar, giving it two out of four stars. He said, \"The story fluctuates between the uninspired and the just plain weird and then gets even weirder.\" While he praised the animation and said that the movie \"begins with an intriguing premise\", he concluded that it \"doesn't come close to fully fleshing out the possibilities\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/2020/2/27/21152865/onward-review-worst-pixar-movie-disney-tom-holland-chris-pratt|title='Onward' a step backward for Disney-Pixar|last=Roeper|first=Richard|date=March 17, 2020|website=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311015050/https://chicago.suntimes.com/2020/2/27/21152865/onward-review-worst-pixar-movie-disney-tom-holland-chris-pratt|archive-date=March 11, 2020|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Ban and censorship ===\n<!-- There is a likelihood the film was banned in these countries for the depiction of necromancy, as the LGBT reference is very minor and can be cut. -->\nThe film was banned in the [[Arab world|Arab]] countries of [[Kuwait]], [[Oman]], [[Qatar]], and [[Saudi Arabia]], as one female cyclops police officer character in the film named Specter (voiced by Lena Waithe) briefly indicates that she is a [[lesbian]]. The scene in question is a brief scene in which Colt Bronco is lamenting about how Ian and Barley Lightfoot do not respect him as a father figure. Specter then replies to him by saying, \"It's not easy being a new parent\u2014my girlfriend's daughter got me pulling my hair out, okay?\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/disney-onward-banned-multiple-middle-east-markets-lesbian-lgbt-reference-1202876168/|title=Disney/Pixar's 'Onward' Banned In Multiple Middle East Countries Due To Lesbian Reference|last=Wiseman|first=Andreas|date=March 6, 2020|website=Deadline|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307021916/https://deadline.com/2020/03/disney-onward-banned-multiple-middle-east-markets-lesbian-lgbt-reference-1202876168/|archive-date=March 7, 2020|access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/onward-banned-lesbian-kuwait-oman-qatar-saudi-arabia-1203526359/|title='Onward' Banned in Several Middle East Countries Due to Lesbian Reference|last=McNary|first=Dave|date=March 6, 2020|website=Variety|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307131642/https://variety.com/2020/film/news/onward-banned-lesbian-kuwait-oman-qatar-saudi-arabia-1203526359/|archive-date=March 7, 2020|access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/onward-banned-middle-east-gay-reference-1202216026/|title='Onward' Banned in Multiple Middle Eastern Countries, Censored in Russia for Gay Reference|last=Lattanzio|first=Ryan|date=March 6, 2020|website=Indie Wire|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319030705/https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/onward-banned-middle-east-gay-reference-1202216026/|archive-date=March 19, 2020|access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref> Homosexual acts are criminalized in these four aforementioned countries, which are predominantly Muslim, although Kuwait does not criminalize female homosexual acts. However, this ban is not universal, and the film has been screened in [[Bahrain]], the [[United Arab Emirates]], [[Lebanon]], and [[Egypt]].\n\nIn [[Russia]], where the [[Russian gay propaganda law|gay propaganda law]] officially criminalizes the dissemination of LGBT-related content to minors under 18, the Russian dub, handled by [[Disney Character Voices International]], changed the line to \"It's not easy being a new parent\u2014my partner's daughter got me pulling my hair out, okay?\" instead. The Russian dub also avoided referring to Specter with gender-specific pronouns.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official|https://movies.disney.com/onward}}\n* {{IMDb title|7146812}}\n\n{{Disney theatrical animated features}}\n{{Pixar}}\n{{Dan Scanlon}}\n\n[[Category:2020 3D films]]\n[[Category:2020 computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:2020 fantasy films]]\n[[Category:2020s American animated films]]\n[[Category:2020s animated films]]\n[[Category:2020s computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:2020s fantasy-comedy films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:American animated fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy-comedy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:Cartoon controversies]]\n[[Category:Censored films]]\n[[Category:Epic fantasy films]]\n[[Category:Films about brothers]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Dan Scanlon]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Jeff Danna]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Mychael Danna]]\n[[Category:Films set on fictional planets]]\n[[Category:High fantasy films]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related animated films]]\n[[Category:Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema]]\n[[Category:Pixar animated films]]\n[[Category:Walt Disney Pictures films]]\n", "name_user": "GoingBatty", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Onward_(film)"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Karnataka", "text_new": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Karnataka, India}}\n{{Consensus |'''Warning:''' Before making significant changes to categories, please discuss first in the [[Talk:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Karnataka|Talk]] page and Sign your comments so that we can reach consensus on how to capture origin, source, cluster, etc.}}\n\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Karnataka\n| map1            = India Karnataka COVID-19 map.svg\n| legend1         = Map of districts with confirmed cases (as of 17 April 2020)\n{{legend|#d45500|30+ confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#ff9955|10\u201329 confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#ffe6d5|1\u20139 confirmed cases}}\n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Karnataka]], [[India]]\n| first_case      = [[Bangalore Urban district|Bengaluru Urban]]\n| arrival_date    = 9 March 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=03|day1=09|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]]\n| confirmed_cases = {{stringsplit | txt={{wdib|ps=1|P1603|qual=P585|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}} |sep=\"--\" |idx=-1}}<ref name=\"KADB\">{{cite web|title=COVID - 19, DASHBOARD|url=https://karunadu.karnataka.gov.in/hfw/kannada/Pages/cv-dashboard-old.aspx|website=karunadu.karnataka.gov.in|access-date=11 April 2020|archive-url=|archive-date=4 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| recovery_cases  = {{stringsplit | txt={{wdib|ps=1|P8010|qual=P585|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}} |sep=\"--\" |idx=-1}}<ref name=\"KADB\"/>\n| deaths          = {{stringsplit | txt={{wdib|ps=1|P1120|qual=P585|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}} |sep=\"--\" |idx=-1}}<ref name=\"KADB\"/>\n| territories     = [[Bangalore Urban district|Bengaluru Urban]], [[Ballari district|Ballari]], [[Gulbarga district|Kalaburagi]], [[Kodagu district|Kodagu]], [[Chikkaballapura district|Chikkaballapura]], [[Mysore district|Mysuru]], [[Dharwad district|Dharwad]], [[Dakshina Kannada district|Dakshina Kannada]], [[Uttara Kannada district|Uttara Kannada]], [[Udupi district|Udupi]], [[Davanagere district|Davanagere]], [[Tumakuru district|Tumakuru]], [[Bidar district|Bidar]], [[Bagalkot district|Bagalkote]], [[Belgaum district|Belagavi]], [[Bangalore Rural district|Bengaluru Rural]], [[Mandya district|Mandya]], [[Gadag district|Gadag]], [[Bijapur district, Karnataka|Vijayapura]], [[Chitradurga district|Chitradurga]]\n| website         = {{url|https://karunadu.karnataka.gov.in/hfw}}\n}}\nThe [[2019-2020 coronavirus pandemic]] was first confirmed on 9 March 2020, in [[Karnataka]] state. The outbreak has been declared an [[epidemic]] in Karnataka, where provisions of the [[Epidemic Diseases Act, 1897]] have been invoked.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Karnataka becomes first state to invoke provisions of Epidemic Diseases Act, 1897 amid COVID-19 fear |url=https://www.deccanherald.com/state/top-karnataka-stories/coronavirus-karnataka-becomes-first-state-to-invoke-provisions-of-epidemic-diseases-act-1897-amid-covid-19-fear-812850.html |accessdate=13 March 2020 |work=Deccan Herald |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322162853/https://www.deccanherald.com/state/top-karnataka-stories/coronavirus-karnataka-becomes-first-state-to-invoke-provisions-of-epidemic-diseases-act-1897-amid-covid-19-fear-812850.html |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> As of 17 April 2020, there have been 359 confirmed cases with 88 recoveries and 13 deaths in the state.<ref name=\"karunadu17apr\"/>\n\n==Timeline of events==\n{{main|Timeline of the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/India/Karnataka medical cases chart}}\n\n=== February ===\n\n*'''On 24 February, '''IT professional who worked at a tech park in the outskirts of [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]] and stayed in a PG accommodation. He traveled to [[Dubai]] on an assignment on February 15 and returned to [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]] on February 20. He attended office for two days - February 20 and 21 - before taking the bus to [[Hyderabad]] in neighboring [[Telangana]]. His samples had tested positive on February 24 in [[Hyderabad]].<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|title=One Intel employee in Bengaluru potentially exposed to coronavirus, under quarantine|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/internet/one-intel-employee-in-bengaluru-potentially-exposed-to-coronavirus-under-quarantine/articleshow/74470605.cms|website=economictimes.indiatimes.com|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405042344/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/internet/one-intel-employee-in-bengaluru-potentially-exposed-to-coronavirus-under-quarantine/articleshow/74470605.cms|archive-date=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== March ===\n\n*'''On 9 March,''' Software engineer of [[Dell]], who traveled from [[Texas]] on 28 February via [[New York City|New York]] and  [[Dubai]], before arriving at [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]] on 1 March, is found to be positive for corona virus. His wife and daughter along with one of his colleagues are admitted to a hospital. The colleague showed flu-like symptoms.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|title=India COVID-19 coronavirus by city and state|url=https://www.pharmaceutical-technology.com/news/india-covid-19-coronavirus-updates-status-by-state/|website=Pharmaceutical Technology|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317222855/https://www.pharmaceutical-technology.com/news/india-covid-19-coronavirus-updates-status-by-state/|archive-date=17 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*'''On 10 March, '''The employee of [[Mindtree]] came back to [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]] from an overseas trip. He was tested positive. The [[Dell]] employee's wife and daughter too have been tested positive and have been isolated under medical supervision.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|title= India COVID-19 coronavirus by city and state|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/two-dell-mindtree-employees-tested-positive-for-coronavirus/articleshow/74575813.cms?from=mdr|website=economictimes.indiatimes.com|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n*'''On 12 March, '''A 26-year-old man, an employee of [[Google]] who came from a trip to [[Greece]], is confirmed to be positive for coronavirus, according to the state health department.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|author=Rashmi Belur|title= Coronavirus: Holiday for all LKG, UKG, pre-primary schools in Bengaluru due to COVID-19 |url=https://www.deccanherald.com/city/top-bengaluru-stories/coronavirus-holiday-for-all-lkg-ukg-pre-primary-schools-in-bengaluru-due-to-covid-19-811899.html |newspaper=Deccan Herald|date=9 March 2020}}</ref> In addition, his wife did not disclose their travel history and having evaded protocols traveled back to her home town of [[Agra]] in [[Uttar Pradesh]].  The country's first death due to corona virus has been reported from Karnataka after the state confirmed that samples of the deceased 76-year-old man from [[Gulbarga|Kalaburagi]] were positive. The man had returned from [[Saudi Arabia]] on February 29.<ref name=\":4\"/>\n*'''On 15 March, '''The new case is the daughter of the 76-year-old [[Kalaburagi]] man who died last week and was found to have corona virus.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|title= Kin of Karnataka COVID-19 victim tests positive, 7th case in state|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/kin-karnataka-covid-19-victim-tests-positive-7th-case-state-120284|website=thenewsminute.com|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n*'''On 16 March, '''A 32-year-old man, who returned from [[United States|the US]] via [[London]] earlier this month, tested positive. He had returned from [[United States|the US]] via [[London]] on March 8 by the same flight as the patient #4 ([[Mindtree]] employee) who had tested positive.<ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|title=US returnee tests positive for virus, cases touch 8 in Karnataka|url=https://www.firstpost.com/health/coronavirus-outbreak-live-updates-covid-19-who-pandemic-quarantine-india-noida-bangalore-cases-alert-novel-latest-news-today-ipl-school-college-8152371.html|website=firstpost.com|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316172608/https://www.firstpost.com/health/coronavirus-outbreak-live-updates-covid-19-who-pandemic-quarantine-india-noida-bangalore-cases-alert-novel-latest-news-today-ipl-school-college-8152371.html|archive-date=16 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*'''On 17 March, '''Three more cases reported- The first, patient is a 20-year-old woman who had travelled to the [[United Kingdom]]. The second one, 63-year-old doctor that treated the senior citizen who died recently of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] in [[Kalaburagi]].<ref name=\":7\">{{cite web|title=Coronavirus: 2 new Covid-19 cases in Karnataka, total 10|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-covid-19-karnataka-2-new-cases-1656255-2020-03-17|website=indiatoday.in|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317204120/https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-covid-19-karnataka-2-new-cases-1656255-2020-03-17|archive-date=17 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":8\">{{cite web|title=Karnataka doctor who treated Coronavirus-infected man tests positive|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/karnataka-doctor-who-treated-coronavirus-infected-man-tests-positive/articleshow/74668969.cms|website=Economic Times|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319195529/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/karnataka-doctor-who-treated-coronavirus-infected-man-tests-positive/articleshow/74668969.cms|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In another case reported, a 67year old female resident  of  [[Bengaluru]]  returned from [[Dubai]] via [[Goa]] on 9 March.  She is a known case of  chronic  kidney  disease.<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|title= Another coronavirus case in Bengaluru: 67-year-old, who returned from Dubai, tests positive|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/another-coronavirus-case-bengaluru-67-year-old-who-returned-dubai-tests-positive-120456}}</ref>\n*'''On 18 March, '''Three more positive cases reported in [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]]. The first, 56-year-old man who returned from [[United States|the US]] on March 6. The second, 26-year-old woman who returned from [[Spain]].<ref name=\":10\">{{cite web|title=Two more positive coronavirus cases reported in Bengaluru|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/two-more-positive-coronavirus-cases-reported-in-bengaluru/articleshow/74689486.cms|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318195037/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/two-more-positive-coronavirus-cases-reported-in-bengaluru/articleshow/74689486.cms|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The third, 35-year-old man who returned from [[United States|US]] on March 10.<ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/state/top-karnataka-stories/three-more-covid-19-cases-in-karnataka-number-goes-up-to-14-815035.html|title=Three more COVID-19 cases in Karnataka, number goes up to 14|date=2020-03-18|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329082829/https://www.deccanherald.com/state/top-karnataka-stories/three-more-covid-19-cases-in-karnataka-number-goes-up-to-14-815035.html|archive-date=29 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*'''On 19 March, '''One more positive case confirmed in [[Kodagu district|Kodagu]] with travel history to [[Saudi Arabia]]. The person arrived at Bengaluru from Dubai on March 15.<ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/state/karnataka-districts/kodagu-records-first-positive-case-of-covid-19-815389.html|title=Kodagu records first positive case of COVID-19|date=2020-03-19|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329082832/https://www.deccanherald.com/state/karnataka-districts/kodagu-records-first-positive-case-of-covid-19-815389.html|archive-date=29 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*'''On 21 March, '''Five positive cases were reported in the state. The first is a 53-year-old woman from [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]]. She was a housemaid for case-11, a female of 67 year old who was confirmed as positive on March 17. The second and the third are from [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]] of age 39 and 21 years respectively. While the former returned from [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands|The Netherlands]] on 19 March and the latter from [[Scotland]] on 17 March. The fourth, a 32-year-old man with travel history to [[Mecca]] from [[Gauribidanur]] in [[Chikkaballapura district|Chikkaballapura]].<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/state/top-karnataka-stories/man-from-gauribidanur-in-karnataka-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-816011.html|title=Man from Gauribidanur in Karnataka tests positive for coronavirus|date=2020-03-19|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321124652/https://www.deccanherald.com/state/top-karnataka-stories/man-from-gauribidanur-in-karnataka-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-816011.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The fifth, is a 35-year-old male from Mysore who arrived at [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]] on 19 March from [[Dubai]].<ref name=\":14\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.prajavani.net/district/bengaluru-city/5-cases-in-one-day-714221.html|title=\u0c92\u0c82\u0ca6\u0cc7 \u0ca6\u0cbf\u0ca8 5 \u0caa\u0ccd\u0cb0\u0c95\u0cb0\u0ca3|date=2020-03-22|website=Prajavani|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322004528/https://www.prajavani.net/district/bengaluru-city/5-cases-in-one-day-714221.html|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":15\">{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://karunadu.karnataka.gov.in/hfw/kannada/nCovDocs/21-03-2020(English).pdf|title=MEDIA BULLETIN: Till date Twenty COVID-19 positive cases have been confirmed in the state which includes one death|date=|work=GOVERNMENT OF KARNATAKA, DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND FAMILY WELFARE SERVICES,BENGALURU|access-date=|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322004528/https://karunadu.karnataka.gov.in/hfw/kannada/nCovDocs/21-03-2020(English).pdf|archive-date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n*'''On 23 March, '''Seven positive cases were reported in the state. Two of them (P#27, P#33) are from [[Kerala]] with travel history to [[Dubai]] and currently being treated at [[Mysore|Mysuru]] & [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]] respectively. All remaining five cases are from [[Bengaluru]], four with travel history (P#28, P#29, P#31, P#32)- from [[Dubai]], [[United Kingdom|UK]], [[United Kingdom|UK]] and [[Germany]] and one being a local transmission - P#30 who is the wife of P#17.<ref name=\"karunadu23\">{{cite web|url=https://karunadu.karnataka.gov.in/hfw/kannada/nCovDocs/23-03-2020(English).pdf|title=NOVEL CORONAVIRUS (COVID-19)MEDIA BULLETIN|website=karunadu.karnataka.gov.in|access-date=23 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323151523/https://karunadu.karnataka.gov.in/hfw/kannada/nCovDocs/23-03-2020(English).pdf|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*'''On 24 March, '''Eight new cases were reported including 3 transit passengers of [[Kerala]] who have landed in airports and being treated in [[Karnataka]].<ref name=\"karunadu24mar\">{{Cite web|url=https://karunadu.karnataka.gov.in/hfw/kannada/nCovDocs/24-03-2020(English).pdf|title=Media Bulletin|last=|first=|date=|website=Drpartment of health and family welfare services,Karnataka|url-status=live|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"toi24\">{{Cite web