ore = 8/10<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.spin.com/2010/08/walkmen-lisbon-fat-possum/ |title=The Walkmen, \u2018Lisbon\u2019 (Fat Possum) |work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |date=August 23, 2010 |accessdate=October 10, 2015 |last=Fennessey |first=Sean}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]''\n| rev10Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite journal |title=The Walkmen: Lisbon |work=[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]] |issue=162 |date=November 2010 |page=110}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Lisbon''''' is the sixth studio album by New York-based group [[The Walkmen]], released on September 14, 2010 in the [[United States of America|US]]. [[John Congleton]] produced and engineered the album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bellaunion.com/index.php/site/news/the_walkmen_sign_to_bella_union/ |title=The Walkmen sign to Bella Union |accessdate=August 4, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100722201133/http://www.bellaunion.com/index.php/site/news/the_walkmen_sign_to_bella_union |archivedate=July 22, 2010 }}</ref> The band recorded nearly thirty tracks before settling on the eleven tracks that comprise the album.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kurp |first=Josh |url=http://encoremag.com/new-york/articles/3630/interview-with-peter-bauer-of-the-walkmen |title=Interview with Peter Bauer of the Walkmen - Encore Magazine: New York |publisher=Encoremag.com |date=2010-07-29 |accessdate=2012-02-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226212111/http://encoremag.com/new-york/articles/3630/interview-with-peter-bauer-of-the-walkmen |archivedate=2012-02-26 }}</ref> The album is a tribute to the city of [[Lisbon]] in [[Portugal]].\n\n''[[Exclaim!]]'' named ''Lisbon'' as the No. 13 Pop & Rock Album of 2010.<ref name=\"Exclaim!'s Year in Review - Top Pop & Rock Albums of 2010\">{{cite web|title=Pop & Rock Year in Review|work=[[Exclaim!]]|url=http://exclaim.ca/Features/YearInReview/pop_rock_year_in_review_2010/Page/13}}</ref> ''Pitchfork'' named it the No. 21 in their Top 50 Albums of 2010.<ref name=\"Pitchfork Staff list: The Top 50 Albums of 2010\">{{cite web|title=Pitchfork Staff list: The Top 50 Albums of 2010|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|url=http://pitchfork.com/features/staff-lists/7893-the-top-50-albums-of-2010/3/}}</ref>\n\nAs of 2011 it has sold 39,159 copies in United States according to [[Nielsen SoundScan]]. <ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20130421005740/http://marathonpacks.tumblr.com/post/2728942718/data</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n|headline   =  Standard Edition\n|all writing = The Walkmen\n|title1  =  Juveniles\n|length1  =  4:27\n|title2  =  Angela Surf City\n|length2  =  3:23\n|title3  =  Follow the Leader\n|length3  =  2:01\n|title4  =  Blue as Your Blood\n|length4  = 4:16\n|title5  =  Stranded\n|length5  =  4:27\n|title6  =  Victory\n|length6  =  4:06\n|title7  = All My Great Designs\n|length7  =  4:42\n|title8 =  Woe Is Me\n|length8  =  3:29\n|title9  =  Torch Song\n|length9  =  4:07\n|title10  =  While I Shovel the Snow\n|length10  =  4:00\n|title11  =  Lisbon\n|length11  =  5:56\n|total_length = 44:55\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n|collapsed = yes\n|headline  =  Bonus disc track listing\n|title12  =  All Black and White\n|length12  =  2:47\n|title13  = Grateful\n|length13  =  3:52\n|title14  =  Orange Sunday\n|length14  =  3:20\n|title15  =  Paper House\n|length15  =  3:39\n|total_length  =  58:30\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[AllMusic]].<ref name=\"allmusic-album-credits\">{{cite web | url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/lisbon-mw0002024119/credits | title=Lisbon - The Walkmen album credits | publisher=[[AllMusic]] | accessdate=10 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''Band'''\n*Matt Barrick  \u2013 Drums \n*Peter Bauer   \u2013  Organ, Piano\n*Walter Martin   \u2013  Bass, Percussion\n*Hamilton Leithauser   \u2013  Guitar, Vocals\n*Paul Maroon  \u2013  Guitar, Trumpet, Viola\n\n'''Additional musicians'''\n*[[Alec Ounsworth]]   \u2013 Vocals\n*Greg Glassman   \u2013 Trumpet\n*Rachel Golub   